<p>Well, that's because that's exactly what it is.</p>
<p>The Hand isn't a monolith, and each Hand article has multiple contributors. That's just the POV of one of the more radical Hand members &#8212; who, I agree, is being pretty unfair. The writer of the hub intro piece would also agree that's unfair, too, even (probably taking the POV that the Foundation <em>cares</em> about scientific inquiry, but are hampering themselves out of sheer fear &#8212; a POV that's more fairly reflected in established material). But&#8230; the more unfair POV still exists. Hell, <em>more</em> extreme perspectives exist.</p>
<p>Post-contest I'll add a footnote disagreeing with it, and/or change that into a footnote or alter it in some other way. Because why not, eh? If you come away thinking that's meant to represent the Hand's POV overall, others may, too.</p>

