<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">SCP-001?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">What?&nbsp;One&nbsp;can&nbsp;speculate,&nbsp;right?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>SCP-001.</strong><br />
<strong>Description:</strong> The Foundation is a memetic phenomenon that has persisted across the ages as a way to protect humanity from knowledge of the anomalous and knowledge that is anomalous in itself (quite often an overlapping concept). While the origin of this phenomenon has not been clearly determined, as is usual with memes of its magnitude, SCP-001 has been deemed not only primordial, but directly responsible for the existence of the Foundation itself. (&#8230;)</p>
<p><strong>The Jailor's Dream.</strong><br />
<strong>Conspectus:</strong> The End of Dreams, also referred to in this day and age as &quot;the Foundation&quot;, &quot;the Jailor's Dream&quot; or &quot;the Not-Mind&quot; is a conscious thought that can take root in all but most powerful of minds and, theoretically, wishes to prevent the Children of Dust from ever taking hold over knowledge of the Ways, the Library and the anomalous as a whole. The first cause of the End of Dreams remains removed and unattainable for the Serpent's Hand, and the archivists will not reveal any information on neither its origin nor its actual entity&#8230;</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

